<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870326-0155 </DOCNO><HL> Centerior Energy UnitIs Granted 3% Rate Boost</HL><DD> 03/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CXUTILITIES (UTI) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Centerior Energy Corp.'s Cleveland Electric Illuminating Co. unit was granted a 3% rate increase by the Public Utilities Commission of Ohio.    The boost, expected to generate $40 million in annual revenue, will take effect in the next several days. The company said the increase coincides with a decrease of about the same amount in the company's fuel charges, which are adjusted twice a year. The decrease went into effect in early March. </TEXT></DOC>